ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It is a really good course to learn the basics of ecology, and how to apply ecological ideas to paleontology, to make the field of paleoecology. I recommend it to any student who does not have a strong background in ecology, because if they do, it might be too basic.
You read the most important papers of ecology and then read a paper that tries to adapt this concept to the fossil record. I would recommend the class if someone was interested in ecology.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: IT deepened my knowledge of paleoecology a lot, because I had basically never learned anything about it before. It will probably not apply much to my dissertation research, though, since I don't plan to have much of an ecological component.
It gave me some ideas of what hasn't been done with the fossil record yet.
